Switzerland's three major banks haveoffered Argentina an extra 110.5 mln Swiss franc credit to helpfinance the building of a heavy water plant there by GebruederSulzer AG &lt;SULZ.Z>, Union Bank of Switzerland, UBS said.    The three -- UBS, Credit Suisse and Swiss Bank Corp --provided an initial 409 mln franc credit after Argentina signeda contract with Sulzer in 1980. The plant will supply itsnuclear power industry.    The extra credit, provided at market rates, covers extracosts incurred due to building delays, a UBS spokesman said. REUTER&#3;